
[1]abolition

   ABOLI'TION, n. abolishun. The act of abolishing; or the state of being
   abolished; an annulling; abrogation; utter destruction; as the
   abolition of laws, decrees, ordinances, rites, customs, debts, &c.

   The application of this word to persons and things, is now unusual or
   obsolete. To abolish persons, canals and senses, the language of good
   writers formerly, is no longer legitimate.
